    <div> The oil-exporting nations are starting to diversify their economies which means they have new investment opportunities at home that did not exist before . China still has a very large capital surplus , but that is likely to decline as domestic consumption grows and as the renminbi continues to appreciate , and in the meantime , the authorities have announced their intention to divert some</div>
